public abstract static class Invoker.Unit
extends Object
implements Runnable

The unit encapsulates a unit of executable code that will be run on the invoker thread. It also provides facilities for additional code to be run on the main thread once the primary code has completed on the invoker thread.

Method Detail

invoke

public abstract boolean invoke()
This method is called on the invoker thread and should be used to perform the primary function of the unit. It can return true to cause the handleResult() method to be subsequently invoked on the dobjmgr thread (generally to allow the results of the invocation to be acted upon back in the context of the regular world) or false to indicate that no further processing should be performed.

Returns:
true if the handleResult() method should be called on the main thread, false if not.

handleResult

public void handleResult()
Invocation unit implementations can implement this function to perform any post unit invocation processing back on the main thread. It will be invoked if invoke() returns true.

run

public void run()
Specified by:
run in interface Runnable

getLongThreshold

public long getLongThreshold()
Returns the duration beyond which this invoker unit will be considered to be running too long and result in a warning being logged. The default is 500ms.

getDetail

public String getDetail()
Detail specific to this invoker to be included with the warning if this invoker takes longer than the long threshold. By default, no detail is included.

toString

public String toString()
Returns the name of this invoker.
